===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=枪|t2=鎗}}
{{wp|zh:,lzh:,wuu:枪}}
{{rfe|zh|The modern Sinitic meaning of "gun" (which none of the Sino-Xenic languages use; {{och-l|銃}} is used instead, while 槍 retains the original "spear" meaning) supposedly stems from a shortening of {{w|lang=zh|突火槍}}, aka the "fire lance", an early proto-gun invented around the Song dynasty.<ref>https://www.reddit.com/r/ChineseLanguage/comments/1ekbx7w/why_does_枪_have_the_木字旁/</ref>

As for further etymology, doesn't seem to be given etymology by STEDT or Schuessler (2007), though note a vague resemblance in the Old Chinese pronunciation to {{ncog|my|လှံ|t=spear}}.}}

